      • wherePivot

        public static int wherePivot(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> list)
        Returns the index of a list where it can be split into half and the values before and after the index will be the closest to one another.
        Parameters:
        list - the given list to be "balanced".
        Returns:
        the index in which the list is balanced. Notice that it's the limit counting from left to right. eg: [1,2,3,4,5] returns 2. returns -1 for any array of length less than 2. eg: [],[1], they can't be balanced.
